Robert M. Deardorff, a freelance travel writer, died yesterday in Paris. He was 61 years old and lived in Rome.

Mr. Deardorff, a graduate of Columbia University's Graduate School of Journalism, was for over 20 years a contributor to the Sunday Travel Section of The New York Times. He specialized in articles on Italy, Switzerland, France and Belgium.

He went to Rome in 1952 as correspondent for Travel magazine, for which he wrote a regular column. He also contributed articles to Holiday, Redbook, Travel Agent and Passport.

A brother, William, survives.